Cerell Rivera has a 15-year record of accomplishment successfully garnering financial support and public endorsements from thought leaders in different organizations and across all levels of government. Strong relationship building and influencing skills enable Cerell to develop high-profile public, private, and nonprofit collaborations resulting in multi-million dollar engagements. Among her most notable accomplishments, Cerell created philanthropic and social change campaigns that generated in excess of $7mm USD in new public benefits. Additionally, Cerell strategized and deployed public relations and marketing tactics that doubled engagement and increased demand for services by 30-70%. Cerell has a history of successfully managing projects, translating strategic thinking into action, and moving cross-functional teams to desired outcomes. Cerell’s international experience includes overseas residence, Japanese language skills, and intercultural exposure. 

 Specialties: Government and Public Affairs (corporate social responsibility, employee engagement, stakeholder engagement, policy analysis); Program Management (prioritization, execution, delivery); Public Relations & Communications (creation and curation of content, social media strategy, community development); Business Management (strategic planning, operations, budgeting, procurement); Volunteer and Community Service (philanthropy, nonprofits, NGOs, board of directors, foundations, civic engagement, grant writing and administration)
